LeetCode 152. Maximum Product Subarray
Problem

Given an integer array nums, find the contiguous non-empty subarray that has the largest product, and return the product.

Example
nums = [2,3,-2,4]

Subarrays:
[2] = 2
[2,3] = 6
[2,3,-2] = -12
[3,-2,4] = -24
[4] = 4
...

Maximum Product = 6
1. Brute Force
Idea

Generate all possible subarrays and calculate their product.

Algorithm
Fix start index i.
Extend end index j.
Maintain running product.
Update maximum product.
Time Complexity
O(n²)
Space Complexity
O(1)

Code
class Solution {
    public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {

        int n = nums.length;
        int maxProduct = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            int product = 1;

            for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {

                product *= nums[j];
                maxProduct = Math.max(maxProduct, product);
            }
        }

        return maxProduct;
    }
}

2. Prefix and Suffix Product (Better)
Idea

A negative number can flip the sign of the product.

To handle this, compute:

Prefix product from left to right.
Suffix product from right to left.

The answer is the maximum value seen among all prefix and suffix products.

If the running product becomes 0, reset it to 1.

Example
nums = [2,3,-2,4]

Prefix Products:
2, 6, -12, -48

Suffix Products:
4, -8, -24, -48

Maximum = 6
Time Complexity
O(n)
Space Complexity
O(1)

Code
class Solution {
    public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {

        int n = nums.length;

        int prefix = 1;
        int suffix = 1;
        int ans = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            if (prefix == 0) prefix = 1;
            if (suffix == 0) suffix = 1;

            prefix *= nums[i];
            suffix *= nums[n - 1 - i];

            ans = Math.max(ans, Math.max(prefix, suffix));
        }

        return ans;
    }
}

3. Optimal (Kadane Variant: Track Max and Min)
⭐ Key Insight

Unlike Maximum Subarray Sum, multiplication by a negative number swaps maximum and minimum.

Example:

Current Max = 6
Current Min = -3

Multiply by -2:

New Max = (-3) × (-2) = 6
New Min = 6 × (-2) = -12

So we must maintain:

maxProdEndingHere
minProdEndingHere
Formula

If current number is negative, swap maxProd and minProd.

Then:

maxProd=max(nums[i], maxProd×nums[i])

minProd=min(nums[i], minProd×nums[i])

Algorithm
Initialize:
maxProd = nums[0]
minProd = nums[0]
answer = nums[0]
Traverse array.
If current number is negative, swap max and min.
Update max and min products.
Update answer.
Time Complexity
O(n)
Space Complexity
O(1)

Code (Optimal)
class Solution {
    public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {

        int maxProd = nums[0];
        int minProd = nums[0];
        int ans = nums[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {

            if (nums[i] < 0) {
                int temp = maxProd;
                maxProd = minProd;
                minProd = temp;
            }

            maxProd = Math.max(nums[i], maxProd * nums[i]);
            minProd = Math.min(nums[i], minProd * nums[i]);

            ans = Math.max(ans, maxProd);
        }

        return ans;
    }
}

Dry Run
nums = [2,3,-2,4]
i	num	maxProd	minProd	ans
0	2	2	2	2
1	3	6	3	6
2	-2	-2	-12	6
3	4	4	-48	6

Final Answer:

6
Why Do We Need minProd?

Consider:

nums = [-2, 3, -4]

Without tracking the minimum:

-2 × 3 = -6
-6 × (-4) = 24 ✅

The minimum negative product becomes the maximum positive product after multiplying by another negative.

